R1: All seemed like simple, everyday tasks. Other than starting a conversation, which at times would not be all that appropriate. The individual scenario would need to be judged.
R2: As before, we do not know the relationship of the individuals or the situation they are in, so it may or may not be appropriate to start a conversation.
R3: All actions seem appropriate for the setting.
R4: There is someone immediately next to the arrow, so it would be rude to start hoovering or mopping the floor. We could start a conversation but do not know the situation or relationship of the individuals
R5: There is a lot of people in the scene. It might be inappropriate to start hoovering (creating noise) or mopping (creating a slippery floor). It might also be difficult to carry food or drinks safely without bumping into people.
R6: There is a small child nearby, so it may not be safe to carry hot food or drinks due to the possibility of bumping into them or tripping over.
R7: There is a lot of people in the scene, so hoovering might cause a lot of noise. Picking up and cleaning items would be acceptable, as long as it was safe to do so and not a risk of bumping into people.
R8: There is enough other people in the scene that hoovering and creating noise would not be a good idea. It would be acceptable to start a conversation though, as it looks like a social gathering.
R9: It looks like a relaxed atmosphere within the scene, with a fairly large group of people. One person is relaxing on the sofa, so hoovering would be inappropriate as would cause noise. Starting a conversation seems a good thing to do in this party like atmosphere.
R10: It looks like a group within the scene are having a conversation. Whilst carrying food and drink and small objects would likely not interrupt them, hoovering or moving large objects/furniture would be inappropriate.
R11: There is music playing, so hoovering would not be appropriate as would drown out the sound of the music. Starting a conversation would be acceptable, as there is a group of people in a relaxed place.
R12: People are relaxing on the sofa in this scene. They would be disturbed by anything that would cause noise, such as hoovering or moving furniture. Quietly carrying small objects or drinks or food would be acceptable.
R13: There is nobody else in the scene, so it would be a great time to hoover or move furniture/large objects around, as people would not be affected by the noise.
R14: People are relaxing in the scene. Children are also present. The hoover would cause noise, and so is not suitable or appropriate for the setting.
R15: Mopping might cause the floor to be sloppy, and therefore someone to slip.
R16: There is music playing, hoovering would ruin the sound and therefore would not be a good idea.
R17: There are a couple of other people in the room, so it might not be a good idea to vacuum and disturb them.
R18: Hoovering might disturb the two people nearby. Mopping might cause the floor to be slippy. Carrying small objects carefully would be acceptable.
R19: There is only one other person nearby, so all actions are appropriate, with the exception of hoovering which may cause audio disturbance, but is likely to be not too much of a problem as the other person is a distance away.
R20: There is a lot of people nearby, including children who could get in the way of carrying items, and potentially pose a safety risk.
